##Support for resumption of work, "THREE BARRELS OF OIL" gas price reduction why sad two power grid price reduction

Weixin caijingEleven

The function introduction by "CAIJING" Magazine Company Industry Report team to create, discuss the success or failure of the enterprise, explore the rise and fall of the industry, promote sunshine business

The National Development and Reform Commission notice called for an early end to the peak season price of natural gas and a cut in the benchmark gate price. As for the specific price reduction, how much of the gas consumption cost relief upstream and downstream enterprises to bear? It's a moot point

Xu Peiyu | Wen

Mark | editor

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Two days after the announcement of the price cut by the National Development and Reform Commission, natural gas distributors have yet to work out the details of the price cut.

On Feb. 22, the National Development and Reform Commission issued separate notices to reduce the cost of gas and electricity for businesses in order to support the resumption of production. Within a day of the announcement, the State Grid Corporation of China and China Southern Power Grid Corporation immediately responded that they would bear the relevant costs themselves and reduce or waive about 59.5 billion yuan of electricity bills for large industrial and commercial enterprises. As of press time, there was no response from petrochina, Sinopec and CNOOC, the three major upstream natural gas companies.

The three oil companies can not be entirely blamed for the slow response to price cuts. From the point of view of the sales process, the implementation of gas price reduction is more difficult than electricity price reduction. Most companies do not buy their gas directly from the big three, but from distributors such as city gas companies. Most of the distributors to gas enterprises sales price, is not entirely market-based pricing, but also subject to the approval of the local government departments. So the question is, if gas prices are to be reduced, how much should the upstream and downstream companies each bear?

The National Development and Reform Commission is also well aware of the difficulty of reducing gas prices. In the announcement of the price reduction, the specific scope of the price reduction, implementation time and other factors. The two grid companies can quickly calculate how much they need to pay. In the notice of the price reduction, the wording was more indecisive. In addition to the explicit requirement for non-residents to use valve station prices in advance to implement the off-season price policy, there is no other quantitative standard, only the "lowest possible price level" and other words. How much gas consumption fee should the natural gas sales enterprise reduce or waive for non-resident users? It wasn't clear in the memo.

Industry insiders expect that the three major oil companies may have to wait a few days to announce the details of the price. "The leaders held a two-day meeting over the weekend to discuss the price reduction measures, and the details have not yet been decided, " a middle-level official from CNPC's natural gas sales company told CAIJING.

A number of city gas companies told the "CAIJING" reporter said that the upstream enterprises have not yet received the price reduction notice, is communicating with the local government specific price reduction measures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
How big is the cut

The end of November to mid March is the peak season for natural gas sales. During this period, gas upstream enterprises sold to distributors of non-residential Gas Wholesale Price, generally higher than the off-season price of about 20% . The only definite price cut in the policy is that the peak season price, which is about 20% higher, will end nearly a month earlier.

The National Development and Reform Commission said in a notice issued on the 22nd that natural gas production and operation enterprises should advance the implementation of off-season prices, for non-residential gas whose prices have been liberalized, natural gas production and operation enterprises are encouraged to fully negotiate and communicate with downstream gas enterprises according to the market situation, lower the price level.

Unlike the policy of Electricity Price Reduction, which is clearly proposed from February 1,2020, the starting time of gas price reduction is not clear. The notice only expressly states that the notice is valid until 30 June 2020.

CAIJING reporter comprehensive information learned that individual regions have implemented the policy of reducing gas prices before the above-mentioned notice was issued, so the starting time of national gas prices is not convenient to unify. In addition to the local price rules of the formulation cycle is different, it is difficult to unify the price reduction time.

According to the original National Development and Reform Commission notice, in addition to ending the peak season ahead of schedule, prices should also be appropriately adjusted downward based on the benchmark gate station price. As for the specific number of floating down, mainly depends on the attitude of petrochina, Sinopec and CNOOC, the three major upstream gas enterprises.

Prior to the announcement by the National Development and Reform Commission, Hubei, Zhejiang, Anhui and other places have announced local gas price reduction measures, most of the region's gas prices fell by 10% , but the implementation time varies. Hubei Province, the longest implementation cycle: January 1 to June 30, small and medium-sized enterprises in Hubei Province industrial gas prices by the benchmark price cut 10% implementation. The policy of Anhui Province is to reduce the price of natural gas used by small, medium-sized and micro-industrial enterprises by 10% , and to reduce the short-run price of the provincial natural gas development corporation by 10% on the basis of the current price for a period of 3 months.

The National Development and Reform Commission has cut the price of electricity to non residents nationwide by 5% . How much will the three upstream natural gas sales enterprises cut the price of the base stations? As of press time, the three enterprises did not respond to the "finance and economics" reporter questions.

Previously all over the price reduction has been announced, whether it will be further increased after the upstream price reduction? It's a moot point. "We just need to keep a reasonable price difference. The next price increase will be announced by the government, " a city gas company official, who had been asked by local governments to lower prices, told CAIJING.

The announcement from the National Development and Reform Commission did not specify how much gas prices would be reduced, but several press releases said it was expected to reduce enterprise electricity and gas costs by more than 63 billion yuan. According to the two major power grid companies announced 59.5 billion yuan of electricity tariff calculation, natural gas sales enterprises to reduce the cost of gas prices in more than 3 billion yuan.

How to share the cost of price reduction

On the basis of the benchmark station price, the price of non-residential gas also includes the pipeline transportation fee and the gas distribution fee. The adjustment of the benchmark station price is mainly aimed at the three upstream natural gas sales enterprises, and the pipeline and distribution fees are corresponding to the middle and downstream gas distribution companies.

The ratio of the benchmark station price to the retail price of natural gas is usually over 50% , and the pipeline and distribution fee is relatively small. A number of city gas companies to "finance and Economics" reporters said that in accordance with the price reduction in the upstream enterprises will be reduced prices accordingly. But it is difficult to lower prices in the upstream basis for further gas prices.

The National Development and Reform Commission's opinion on gas price cuts for downstream companies is not mandatory. The above-mentioned notice points out that the local price authorities should attach great importance to the work, according to the situation of price reduction in upstream enterprises, reduce the terminal sales price of non-residential gas in a timely manner, and effectively transfer all the price reduction space of the door station link to the end users. We encourage all localities to further reduce the terminal sales prices of natural gas and release more price reduction dividends by strengthening the supervision of pipeline transportation and gas distribution prices in the provinces.

As for the contents of the notice, chief information officer, a Qingran think tank, explained to Caijing reporters that the upstream enterprises were the main ones to bear the gas price reduction, and that there was room for lowering the pipeline and gas distribution fees of the middle and lower reaches of the enterprises. But Downstream City Gas Company has certain management pressure, reduce price difficulty bigger.

From 2017 to 2019, the average return on assets in the distribution business sector of all city gas enterprises has dropped from 9.4 percent to 6.8 percent, a person from a city gas company who declined to be named told CAIJING. If this time also asks the city gas enterprise to reduce the price, must have the sufficient reason. Once the price of gas distribution is reduced, it is difficult to rise back in the later period.

Another city gas company told CAIJING that government price adjustments for gas distribution generally go through a regulatory process and often take a week or two to complete. It's not something you can change right away.

Regardless of upstream and downstream how to share the cost of price reduction, petrochina will undoubtedly pay the largest cost of the enterprise. Petrochina's sales of natural gas account for more than 80 percent of China's total consumption. In the first half of 2019, the company's operating profit on natural gas and pipelines was 18.302 billion yuan. Previously mentioned gas price reduction of more than 3 billion yuan, the impact on petrochina's operating performance is not small.

A middle-level figure of CNPC group told CAIJING THAT CNPC will firmly implement the policy of price reduction in time of great difficulties. Just hope that the SASAC assessment to give relevant exclusion, do not hit the enthusiasm of the oil staff. It is also hoped that the National Development and Reform Commission will take into account the fact that central energy enterprises have multiple goals and multiple responsibilities in formulating its reform proposals.

The writer is a reporter for CAIJING
